body:
(continuation of https://github.com/rust-lang-nursery/futures-rs/issues/1199 as it looks like a compiler bug after all, important points repeated here)

### Problem

There appear to be an issue in handling traits that have a parent `'static` bound boxed through an await point: the following example fails to compile with `the requirement `for<'r> 'r : 'static` is not satisfied` (note: I'm using generators for simplicity of reproduction, see below for a futures-only example)
```rust
trait Trait: 'static {}
async fn foo(b: Box<Trait + 'static>) -> () {
    let bar = move || { b; () };
    yield
}
```
[(playground link)](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=7ec91101db1560175685897700a47aaa&version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2015)

However, when removing the `'static` bound on `Trait`, it appears to compile correctly, even though the `Box` itself still has the `+ 'static` bound.
```rust
trait Trait {}
async fn foo(b: Box<Trait + 'static>) -> () {
    let bar = move || { b; () };
    yield
}
```
[(playground link)](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=05492dee18f45fa969d7d3469f04add4&version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2015)

### Futures-only version

The error originated in code that looked like:
```rust
use futures::future;                                  
use std::any::Any;                                    
async fn foo(b: Box<Any + Send + 'static>) -> () { 
    await!(future::lazy(move |_| {                    
        b;                                          
        ()                                            
    }))                                               
}    
```
The `Any` being here the trait that has the `'static` bound. This was tested with `futures-rs` at commit https://github.com/rust-lang-nursery/futures-rs/commit/c02ec75a155485ff4b50f21205b6a462851b08e1 and nightly 2018-08-14.

### No generator-only version

I couldn't manage to get a generator-only version to fail: this compiles.
```rust
use std::any::Any;
use std::ops::Generator;
fn send(msg: Box<Any + 'static>) -> impl Generator + 'static {
    || {
        let mut pinned = move || { msg; () };
        yield
    }
}
```
[(playground link)](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=7f9438aec5f66c39a3e5dcd5aeeea57e&version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2015)

### Potentially related issue

This is potentially related to https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/53259, as the same `for<'r>` appears there?
